=== Allophones

- /q/ is realized as \[x ~ χ\] in coda position.
- /ɪ/ and /ɐ/ are, in common speech, realized as mid \[e̞\] and open mid \[ʌ\] or mid \[ɤ̞\], especially by low education level speakers. This usage is considered impolite and “farmer-like” by the élite, so it is recommended to avoid it in formal situations.
- Inexperienced formal speakers may also hypercorrect /ɵ/ to /o/ — by analogy with the formal realisations of e ad a.
- While phonemically long, /iː/ and /uː/ are realized, in common speech, as short \[i\] and \[u\].
- /ɑː/ is realized as rounded [ɒː \~ ɔː] after labial sounds, and fronted to [äː] after palatal sounds.
- Nasals are realized as voiced plosives at the beginning of words: m -> ⁿb, n -> ⁿd, ɲ -> ⁿɟ, ŋ -> ⁿg

